HEADWORD: Xeroderma
<hw>Xe`ro*der"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>xhro`s</grk> dry + <grk>de`rma</grk> skin.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Ichthyosis.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A skin disease
characterized by the presence of numerous small pigmented spots
resembling freckles, with which are subsequently mingled spots of
atrophied skin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xeronate</ent>⟦br⟧
